From Juliana Taiwo-Obalonye, Abuja President Muhammadu Buhari has extended heartfelt commiserations to the governments and people of Turkey and Syria, and those who lost family and friends in the devastating earthquake in the southern Turkish city of Gaziantep. Special Adviser to the President on Media and Publicity, Femi Adesina, he wished those injured a speedy recovery and assures that the prayers and thoughts of Nigerians are with the many affected by this severe disaster and its aftershocks. He assured that as a steadfast friend to Turkey and Syria, Nigeria is ready to offer its full support in any way possible.